    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="433"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4001/20.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 15.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your letter No. 605, of
                    yesterday’s date, which I at once forwarded to His Majesty’s principal secretary
                    of state for foreign affairs, I have the honor to communicate the following
                    telegram, which I have received this morning in reply from Sir Edward Grey:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Please express to Assistant Secretary of State my thanks for message. The
                            friendly attitude of the President and American Government is warmly
                            appreciated by His Majesty’s Government.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Esme Howard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
